646
00:58:17,630 --> 00:58:24,430
* WAY HO WAY HO *
* WAY HO WAY HO...JOE *

647
00:58:24,931 --> 00:58:30,980
* NOW WAY HO WAY HO *
* WE ARE BOUND FOR BETTER WEATHER, TUMMY *

648
00:58:32,147 --> 00:58:39,280
* WAY HO WAY HO *
* WE ARE ALL WAY, JOE *

649
00:59:00,555 --> 00:59:05,310
HEY BOYS! WE WON'T BE ABLE TO SEE MUCH, ALRIGHT?

650
00:59:05,477 --> 00:59:10,525
SO WE GOTTA LISTEN TO THOSE WAVES HITTIN' THAT BAR.
GOTTA TIME IT.

651
00:59:10,858 --> 00:59:16,448
SO I'M GONNA WAIT FOR A LOW, AND THEN WE GO.
WE GOT FAITH IN YOU, SKIP.

652
00:59:16,948 --> 00:59:20,244
ANYTIME YOU'RE READY, YOU JUST GO, BERNIE.
ALRIGHT?

653
01:00:53,725 --> 01:00:55,436
THE COMPASS IS GONE.

654
01:01:23,176 --> 01:01:25,054
FITZY, THE ENGINE DIED.

655
01:01:32,520 --> 01:01:34,647
I'VE GOT IT. I GOT IT.
NAH, YOU DON'T.

656
01:01:40,654 --> 01:01:42,698
YOU GOT ABOUT FIVE SECONDS, BOYS.

657
01:01:42,764 --> 01:01:46,160
IT'S GRAVITY PAD, IT DOESN'T TRACE OUT...
I KNOW!

658
01:01:51,959 --> 01:01:53,376
COME ON, LIGHT UP!

659
01:02:15,486 --> 01:02:17,528
MASKE? GET BACK HERE.

660
01:02:23,370 --> 01:02:27,124
TIDE'S RISING! IT'LL GET US THROUGH.

661
01:02:29,084 --> 01:02:31,086
BUT LET ME KNOW WHAT'S COMING.

662
01:04:24,758 --> 01:04:28,928
HEY FITZ!? WE'VE BEEN OVER THE BAR.
BACK TO SPOTLIGHT.

663
01:04:32,933 --> 01:04:33,976
COMIN' OUT.

664
01:04:48,758 --> 01:04:50,794
WE TURNED TOO LATE!

665
01:04:52,678 --> 01:04:54,680
WE GOTTA BUY TIME BACK!

666
01:04:54,847 --> 01:04:59,517
TELL SYBERT WE NEED 30 DEGREES WITHIN THE
NEXT TWO MINUTES OR WE'LL MISS THAT SHOLE.

667
01:05:01,769 --> 01:05:04,021
30 DEGREES IN THE NEXT TWO MINUTES..

668
01:05:04,189 --> 01:05:07,149
30 DEGREES IN THE NEXT TWO MINUTES..

669
01:05:07,316 --> 01:05:10,527
30 DEGREES IN THE NEXT TWO MINUTES..

670
01:05:11,112 --> 01:05:12,829
30 DEGREES IN THE NEXT TWO MINUTES..

671
01:05:18,243 --> 01:05:21,579
PUTTIN' HER IN REVERSE.
YOU GOTTA LET THE OCEAN PUSH US.

672
01:05:22,872 --> 01:05:24,081
HOLD ON.

673
01:06:28,846 --> 01:06:30,847
MAYBE YOU WANNA BRACE YOURSELF, ELDON.

674
01:06:33,058 --> 01:06:34,476
318...

675
01:06:39,939 --> 01:06:41,899
316...

676
01:06:42,525 --> 01:06:46,844
CLOSE IT DOWN AS SOON AS SHE HITS!

677
01:06:47,321 --> 01:06:48,905
312...

678
01:07:00,082 --> 01:07:02,792
GENTLEMEN! BRACE YOURSELVES.

679
01:07:04,419 --> 01:07:05,670
HOLD ON!

680
01:07:12,134 --> 01:07:13,677
NOW!

681
01:08:17,025 --> 01:08:18,158
WELL...

682
01:08:22,570 --> 01:08:26,866
YOU DID IT! IT BLOODY WELL WORKED, MR.SYBERT!

683
01:08:30,244 --> 01:08:33,664
YOU GOTTA KEEP THE WATER AWAY FROM
THE AIR INLETS OF THE ENGINE.

684
01:08:33,830 --> 01:08:37,208
WE LOSE POWER, WE LOSE OUR PUMPS.

685
01:08:39,169 --> 01:08:42,922
I'M AFRAID, THE WAY WE'RE PULLIN' SO MUCH WATER,
WAVE WILL PULL US OFF THE SHOLE.

686
01:08:47,301 --> 01:08:49,861
FEELS FUNNY NOT MOVIN AROUND, HUH ELDON?

687
01:08:53,515 --> 01:08:56,725
ALRIGHT, LETS GET TO IT.

688
01:09:21,456 --> 01:09:23,791
WE ARE HEADIN' DOWN TO THE LODGE.
EVERTHING OK?

689
01:09:24,166 --> 01:09:26,210
QUITE DOWN NOW, MY GOD!
GIVE ME A BREAK.

690
01:09:26,376 --> 01:09:30,555
I WAS ON MY WAY HOME AND MY CAR'S BEEN OUT INTO A DITCH.
I NEED SOME HELP.

691
01:09:31,423 --> 01:09:33,024
YEAH ALRIGHT, WE LIVE NEARBY.

692
01:09:33,091 --> 01:09:36,210
WE'LL GO BACK TO MY HOUSE. CALL MY BROTHER.
HE CAN TILL YOU OUT. JUMP IN.

693
01:09:40,556 --> 01:09:42,641
THANK YOU.
YOU DON'T GOT A COAT?

694
01:09:42,933 --> 01:09:46,978
YOU CAN MOVE THAT.
WE'RE BRINGIN' THAT FROM ST.MARTIN'S SURVIVORS.

695
01:09:49,647 --> 01:09:53,442
I LEFT MY COAT AT THE COAST GUARD STATION.
GOTTA MAN THERE?

696
01:09:53,609 --> 01:09:54,818
STOP IT.

697
01:09:58,071 --> 01:09:59,906
HE IS NOT THERE NOW RIGHT NOW.
IT'S A...

698
01:10:01,699 --> 01:10:05,953
IT IS BERNIE WEBBER.
YEAH, BERNIE IS A GOOD MAN.

699
01:10:22,885 --> 01:10:25,595
WE CAN'T FIND 'EM WITHOUT A COMPASS, BERNIE.

700
01:10:27,054 --> 01:10:29,098
WE GOT NO IDEA WHERE THEY ARE.

701
01:10:32,351 --> 01:10:33,560
HOLD ON.

702
01:11:05,172 --> 01:11:06,923
YOU OKAY?

703
01:11:07,882 --> 01:11:11,886
YOU OKAY?
I'M HAVIN' A GREAT TIME OUT HERE, BERNIE!

704
01:11:12,053 --> 01:11:13,379
WHOLE LOT! WHOLE LOTTA FUN HERE.

705
01:11:18,349 --> 01:11:19,909
BRACE YOURSELVES!

706
01:11:33,196 --> 01:11:35,907
IT'S REALLY NICE HERE.

707
01:11:43,497 --> 01:11:47,917
TAKE IT, USE IT.
CONSIDER IT DONE.

708
01:11:54,521 --> 01:11:55,982
WHAT'S WRONG WITH IT!?
WE LOST THE PUMPS.

709
01:11:56,049 --> 01:11:59,469
THE PUMPS ARE CHOKIN' THE BREAKERS.
GO CHECK THE CONNECTIONS.

710
01:12:01,972 --> 01:12:03,181
GIVE ME THE LIGHT.

711
01:12:04,557 --> 01:12:09,061
IT'S ONET OF THOSE DAMN...
SOMETIMES I WISH I DIDN'T UNDERSTAND.

712
01:12:10,270 --> 01:12:12,064
SYBERT, WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

713
01:12:14,023 --> 01:12:16,067
WE'RE USIN' EVERY PUMP WE GOT.

714
01:12:17,026 --> 01:12:19,762
THE JAM THE BREAKERS AND
THE PUMPS WOULDN'T TRICKLE.

715
01:12:19,828 --> 01:12:24,241
WE GOT ANOTHER TWO FEET OF WATER BEFORE IT HITS
THE AIR IN ENGINE AND THEN THE SHIP'S DEAD.

716
01:12:24,407 --> 01:12:26,844
JESUS CHRIST.
DO YOU HEAR THAT?

717
01:12:26,910 --> 01:12:32,131
THE TIDE'S RISING WORKIN' US UP THE SHOLE.
FELLAS, THAT GIVE US SOME TIME.

718
01:12:32,832 --> 01:12:35,917
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, MR.SYBERT?
THAT'S SURE, IS BUB.

719
01:12:36,877 --> 01:12:39,796
AS LONG AS THE GENERATORS KEEP THE PUMPS GOIN'.

720
01:12:41,506 --> 01:12:43,649
BY HOWEVER WE BUY SOME MORE TIME.

721
01:12:43,716 --> 01:12:45,926
YOU WANNA BE TO BE THE MAN, SYBERT RIGHT?
WELL NOW YOU ARE THE MAN.

722
01:12:46,677 --> 01:12:49,179
YOU GOT NO WIFE, GOT NO KIDS BACK HOME?

723
01:12:50,848 --> 01:12:55,935
YOU'RE A SINGLE MAN ALWAYS HIDIN' DOWN BELOW.
WHAT DO YOU GOTTA LOSE?

724
01:12:56,102 --> 01:12:57,386
ENOUGH, BROWN.

725
01:13:00,148 --> 01:13:02,107
I'M AFRAID, BROWN.

726
01:13:03,401 --> 01:13:05,193
GOTTA A LIFE, SAME AS YOU.

727
01:13:10,031 --> 01:13:12,825
JUST DON'T SEE SITTIN' AROUND,
TALKIN' ABOUT IT.

728
01:13:17,371 --> 01:13:22,684
STATION CHATHAM, 36500.
STATION CHATHAM, 36500, DO YOU COPY?

729
01:13:22,751 --> 01:13:27,454
STATION CHATHAM,
THIS IS CHIEF BANGS, CG-36383,

730
01:13:27,505 --> 01:13:32,342
POLLOCK LIGHTSHIP, CG-36500, DO YOU COPY?

731
01:13:32,717 --> 01:13:35,929
WHY CAN'T THEY HEAR US, BERNIE?
WE HEAR THEM.

732
01:13:36,095 --> 01:13:40,299
TIDE IS TOO HIGH, ZERO HEAD WAY.
STATION CHATHAM, DO YOU COPY?

733
01:13:40,391 --> 01:13:41,985
I REPEAT, WE'RE COMIN' HOME.

734
01:13:42,051 --> 01:13:45,696
STATION CHATHAM, 36383,
RETURN TO OLD HARBOR.

735
01:13:45,963 --> 01:13:49,316
POLLOCK LIGHTSHIP, CG-36500, DO YOU COPY?

736
01:13:49,482 --> 01:13:51,150
WE ARE ALL ALONE.

737
01:13:51,943 --> 01:13:54,768
YOU HEARD, BANGS, ON THE RADIO LIKE HE'S
OUT GOIN' ALL BACK IN BUT COULDN'T GET OUT...

738
01:13:54,795 --> 01:13:57,723
AND THE STORM'S GETS WORSE...

739
01:13:59,240 --> 01:14:01,009
WE MUST RETURN BACK, WEBBER.

740
01:14:01,577 --> 01:14:05,613
WE'VE COME FARTHER THAN ANYBODY
EVER THOUGHT POSSIBLE, BERNIE!

741
01:14:06,456 --> 01:14:10,918
MAYBE RICHIE IS RIGHT!
MAYBE WE SHOULD JUST GO BACK!

742
01:14:11,085 --> 01:14:17,423
THE WIND IS EIGHT TO NINE.
REPEAT, WIND EIGHT TO NINE. HEAVY SNOWFALL.

743
01:14:17,591 --> 01:14:19,333
YOU HEARD BANGS ON THE RADIO.

744
01:14:19,467 --> 01:14:22,428
WE HAVE NO COMPASS AND
WE HAVE NO WAY TO COMMUNICATE.

745
01:14:25,981 --> 01:14:29,976
YOU ARE...
WHAT? WHAT? I'M WHAT RITCHIE?

746
01:14:31,460 --> 01:14:37,191
I GOT US THIS FAR, DIDN'T I?
NOT BANGS NOT CLUFF, BUT I DID IT!

747
01:14:43,738 --> 01:14:45,240
WE DID IT, RICHIE.

748
01:14:49,159 --> 01:14:50,745
YOU WANNA TURN BACK AROUND?

749
01:14:52,997 --> 01:14:56,299
NO, NOT NOW! WE CAME TOO FAR.

750
01:14:57,000 --> 01:14:58,668
WE ARE NOT GONNA LEAVE 'EM.

751
01:15:01,295 --> 01:15:03,130
NOT ON MY WATCH.

752
01:15:05,633 --> 01:15:07,009
JUST DO YOUR JOB.

753
01:15:11,429 --> 01:15:14,515
HEY FITZ, TURN OFF THE BEAM.
WE'LL WORK IN THE DARK.

754
01:15:14,682 --> 01:15:18,018
WE CAN SEE THE LIGHT OF THE
PENDLETON BETTER IN THE DARK.

755
01:15:25,858 --> 01:15:27,235
WATCH IT.

756
01:15:33,198 --> 01:15:34,441
GET BACK HERE.

757
01:15:36,701 --> 01:15:38,086
GET YOUR BUDS BACK HERE.

758
01:15:38,912 --> 01:15:40,955
I LOST MY HAT.

759
01:16:06,644 --> 01:16:07,953
YOU OKAY?

760
01:16:09,855 --> 01:16:15,694
YEAH, I'M JUST TIRED.
COME ON.

761
01:16:20,406 --> 01:16:22,366
YOU KIDS GO PLAY IN THE BEDROOM, OK?

762
01:16:22,633 --> 01:16:24,777
YOU CAN WAIT.
LET ME CALL MY BROTHER.

763
01:16:24,797 --> 01:16:27,688
THANKS. CALL ME MARIAM.

764
01:16:45,003 --> 01:16:47,380
YOU THINK YOUR MOTHER WOULD
MIND IF I TURN ON THE RADIO?

765
01:16:54,478 --> 01:16:57,314
COAST BOSTON, THIS IS THE UNIMAK.

766
01:16:57,481 --> 01:17:00,558
WE ARE FIRST AT THE MERCER BOW
HER NOW AT THE PORT OF YAKUTAT.

767
01:17:00,624 --> 01:17:04,378
FOUR MERCER CREW MEMBERS JUMPED FROM THE DECK.
ALL ARE LOST.

768
01:17:04,445 --> 01:17:08,866
I REPEAT, FOUR MEN LOST.
SEVERAL CREW MEMBERS HAVE HYPOTHERMIA.

769
01:17:09,032 --> 01:17:13,119
WE'LL WAIT FOR DAYBREAK TO ATTEMPT ANOTHER RESCUE.
OVER.

770
01:17:14,996 --> 01:17:19,658
DOES NO GOOD LISTENIN' TO ALL THAT CHATTER, MARIAM.
BETTER TO LIVE NOT KNOWIN'.

771
01:17:24,552 --> 01:17:26,552
...IT WOULD BE 1900 HOURS...

772
01:17:31,552 --> 01:17:34,554
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN MARRIED TO BERNIE FOR?
WE ARE...

773
01:17:39,308 --> 01:17:41,269
WE'RE NOT MARRIED YET.

774
01:17:43,729 --> 01:17:47,015
I DIDN'T KNOW IF...
LIKE I SAID, BERNIE IS A GOOD MAN.

775
01:17:51,236 --> 01:17:55,573
HIM AND SOME OF THEM OTHERS TRY GETTIN' OUT ONE YEAR AGO SAVED MY HUSBAND ARNIE  
AND THE CREW OF THE LANDRY.

776
01:17:55,948 --> 01:17:59,285
THEY WERE OUT ON THE BOAT NIGHT TIME OFF
NANTUCKET WHEN THE BOAT STARTED TAKIN' WATER.

777
01:17:59,451 --> 01:18:01,203
A NIGHT JUST LIKE THIS.

778
01:18:02,413 --> 01:18:05,165
COME ON, WE GOTTA GET GOIN'.

779
01:18:05,331 --> 01:18:08,576
BROTHER'S ON HIS WAY TO COME MEET US.
I GOTTA GET TO THE LODGE, COME ON, YOU TWO.

780
01:18:42,167 --> 01:18:46,881
BECAUSE PEOPLE SAID SIT DOWN SIT DOWN,
LET YOU ROCK THE BOAT 753

781
01:18:48,215 --> 01:18:53,013
* CAUSE PEOPLE SAID SIT, DOWN SIT DOWN *
* YOU ROCK THE BOAT *

782
01:18:53,180 --> 01:18:58,812
* THE DEVIL YOU CAN PULL DOWN *
* THE SHARP EDGES OF YOUR JACKET *

783
01:19:08,614 --> 01:19:10,375
* SIT DOWN, SIT DOWN, SIT DOWN *

784
01:19:54,694 --> 01:19:56,137
DO YOU KNOW WHO SHE IS?

785
01:19:57,214 --> 01:20:01,335
AIN'T BERNIE'S FAULT, CARLIN.
NO ONE'S FAULT. IT'S LIKE HER BLAMING YOU.

786
01:20:02,387 --> 01:20:03,680
FOR WHAT?

787
01:20:03,847 --> 01:20:07,159
YOU ARE THE ONE THAT TOLD ME THERE WAS NO
OTHER SHIP OUT THERE BECAUSE OF YOU, RIGHT?

788
01:21:24,317 --> 01:21:27,153
FITZ, TURN ON THE SEARCHLIGHT.

789
01:22:15,920 --> 01:22:18,398
I CAN'T BELIEVE WE FOUND HER.
LOOK AT THAT!

790
01:22:22,678 --> 01:22:26,558
WE'RE TOO LATE.
IT'S A GHOST SHIP.

791
01:22:30,946 --> 01:22:33,101
ARE YOU SEEING THIS, SIR?
YEAH.

792
01:22:33,201 --> 01:22:35,901
YEAH, YEAH...I SEE HIM.

793
01:22:35,777 --> 01:22:37,529
NOT SURE I BELIEVE IT!

794
01:22:40,782 --> 01:22:42,952
WHERE IS THE HELL'S HE GOIN'?

795
01:22:51,337 --> 01:22:52,922
GOOD TO SEE YOU BOYS.

796
01:22:59,728 --> 01:23:01,228
CAREFUL.

797
01:23:07,982 --> 01:23:13,154
HOW ARE WE GONNA FIT THEM ALL ON THIS BOAT?
WE WERE TOLD TO FIT ONLY 12, INCLUDING US.

798
01:23:14,665 --> 01:23:16,367
THOSE ARE JUST REGULATION, RIGHT?

799
01:23:20,872 --> 01:23:22,415
HOW MANY COULD YOU FIT?

800
01:23:23,917 --> 01:23:25,502
20, 22 TOPS.

801
01:23:28,131 --> 01:23:29,298
WAIT.

802
01:23:29,465 --> 01:23:31,134
THEY COMIN' OUT HERE.

803
01:23:55,296 --> 01:23:57,173
TRY THE STATION, PORT SIDE.

804
01:24:27,617 --> 01:24:29,578
COME ON, I GOT YOU.

805
01:24:50,311 --> 01:24:51,512
WE GOT YA.

806
01:25:01,282 --> 01:25:02,658
MASKE, GET OVER HERE!

807
01:25:05,120 --> 01:25:07,748
COME ON.
GRAB HIM.

808
01:25:25,060 --> 01:25:26,771
YOU KNOW WHERE YOU GOIN' ON, MISS?

809
01:25:27,855 --> 01:25:29,190
I THINK SO.

810
01:25:29,908 --> 01:25:31,735
THANKS FOR YOUR HELP, MR.NICKERSON.

811
01:25:31,835 --> 01:25:32,935
YEAH.

812
01:25:33,862 --> 01:25:35,164
YOU KNOW...

813
01:25:36,323 --> 01:25:39,119
BERNIE AIN'T OUT THERE, 'CAUSE OF ME.
YEAH, I KNOW.

814
01:25:40,588 --> 01:25:43,040
IT'S BERNIE'S JOB TO GO OUT, RIGHT?

815
01:25:46,544 --> 01:25:48,380
HOW CAN I BLAME ME FOR IT?

816
01:26:03,898 --> 01:26:08,153
NICE AND SLOW! NICE AND SLOW.
PETE, YOU'RE UP NEXT.

817
01:26:08,320 --> 01:26:11,199
TAKE IT NICE AND SLOW! TAKE IT EASY.
COME ON.

818
01:26:19,409 --> 01:26:21,752
WE GOTTA GO!
WE'RE LEAVIN' NOBODY BEHIND.

819
01:26:21,919 --> 01:26:24,614
GO ON THAT LADDER, ELDON.
WE GOTTA GET HIM DOWN.

820
01:26:24,656 --> 01:26:26,356
WE HAVE NO TIME.

821
01:26:26,388 --> 01:26:28,850
SHE'S SLIPPIN'.
WE GOTTA GET OFF THIS SHIP.

822
01:26:29,578 --> 01:26:30,880
HURRY!

823
01:26:31,055 --> 01:26:32,811
ELDON, HOW YOU DOIN'?

824
01:26:34,142 --> 01:26:35,936
I'M SCARED.

825
01:26:42,694 --> 01:26:46,406
WELL...IT'S A LOT SCARIER UP HERE WITHOUT US.
YOU GOTTA LISTEN TO ME!

826
01:26:47,407 --> 01:26:49,763
ELDON?
WE ALL GOTTA GET DOWN! STOP PUSHIN'.

827
01:26:49,802 --> 01:26:54,866
FOLLOW RIGHT BEHIND ME.
IF I COULD DO IT, ANYONE CAN.

828
01:27:08,683 --> 01:27:09,928
COME ON.

829
01:27:24,677 --> 01:27:26,677
HOLD ON, ELDON.

830
01:27:35,965 --> 01:27:38,593
TINY, TINY! HOLD ON.

831
01:28:35,661 --> 01:28:37,905
ELDON.

832
01:28:41,042 --> 01:28:43,837
ELDON, LOOK AT ME.
LOOK AT ME.

833
01:28:56,227 --> 01:28:58,938
WHEN I JUMP SAY, LET GO.
READY?

834
01:29:06,514 --> 01:29:07,648
JUMP.

835
01:29:11,996 --> 01:29:13,264
YOU GOOD?

836
01:29:15,366 --> 01:29:16,666
HOLD ON TIGHT.

837
01:29:22,133 --> 01:29:24,527
ALRIGHT! SO HEAVY, YOU CAN HARDLY STEER.

838
01:29:24,594 --> 01:29:27,547
THEY ARE SAYING THERE ARE
SEVEN OR EIGHT UP THERE ABOARD.

839
01:29:29,349 --> 01:29:34,731
MAYBE...WE TAKE THESE GUYS BACK IN...
COME BACK OUT.

840
01:29:43,074 --> 01:29:46,995
CAN'T LEAVE ANYBODY ALONE.
THAT BOAT WON'T LAST.

841
01:29:49,415 --> 01:29:51,459
WE ALL LIVE OR WE ALL DIE.

842
01:29:54,171 --> 01:29:55,372
RIGHT?

843
01:30:30,789 --> 01:30:32,750
YOU...AA..YOU DID GOOD.

844
01:30:33,600 --> 01:30:36,721
YOU SHOULD BE LAST ONE OFF, MR.SYBERT.

845
01:31:35,248 --> 01:31:36,534
LAST MAN!

846
01:33:16,618 --> 01:33:20,332
HEY FITZ! TURN OFF THAT SEARCHLIGHT, YEAH?

847
01:33:45,402 --> 01:33:47,655
WE HAVE RADIO CONTACT WITH THE MCCULLOUGH.

848
01:33:48,490 --> 01:33:53,120
I SAID THEY HAVE LOST FOUR MEN, BUT SAVED THE REST.
THE CAPTAIN OF THE POLLOCK RIP SAID...

849
01:33:53,287 --> 01:33:58,260
MR.CLUFF, IT IS 36500,
IT'S BERNIE...RIGHT ON THE RADIO!

850
01:33:58,327 --> 01:34:02,365
CHATHAM, CHATHAM, YOU COPY?

851
01:34:02,983 --> 01:34:07,763
CG-36500, THIS STATION CHATHAM.
WEBBER, IS THAT YOU?

852
01:34:07,929 --> 01:34:10,516
YES, SIR, IT'S ME, BERNIE.

853
01:34:11,927 --> 01:34:16,774
WE GOT 32 SURVIVORS ABOARD FROM THE PENDLETON, SIR.

854
01:34:17,783 --> 01:34:19,493
STATION CHATHAM, YOU COPY?

855
01:34:19,860 --> 01:34:25,033
36500, STATION CHATHAM.
DID YOU SAY YOU HAVE 32 SURVIVORS ABOARD!?

856
01:34:25,199 --> 01:34:29,747
THEY RESCUED 'EM! RESCUED 32 OF THEM.
YES SIR, 32...

857
01:34:29,914 --> 01:34:33,276
WE LOST OUR COMPASS,
SO WE DON'T KNOW WHERE WE ARE...

858
01:34:33,418 --> 01:34:35,220
BUT WE'LL TRY TO MAKE IT BACK HOME.

859
01:34:35,554 --> 01:34:37,881
CAN'T COME BACK WITHOUT A COMPASS.
NOT IN THIS WEATHER.

860
01:34:37,919 --> 01:34:39,220
THEY CAN NOT GO BACK.

861
01:34:40,426 --> 01:34:42,262
YOU LOST YOUR COMPASS WEBBER?

862
01:34:42,355 --> 01:34:46,775
NO. 36500, THIS IS THE POLLOCK LIGHTSHIP.
DO NOT PROCEED TO THE SHORE.

863
01:34:47,142 --> 01:34:50,563
WE'RE 5 MILES NORTHEAST OF LAST
LOCATION OF PENDLETON.

864
01:34:50,593 --> 01:34:54,765
PROCEED TO OUR POSITION, OVER.
CG-36500, STATION CHATHAM...

865
01:34:54,969 --> 01:34:59,224
PROCEED TO POLLOCK LIGHTSHIP
AND ONBOARD ALL SURVIVORS.

866
01:35:00,408 --> 01:35:02,035
WHAT DO THEY KNOW, RIGHT?

867
01:35:04,580 --> 01:35:05,822
RIGHT, RICHIE?

868
01:35:06,874 --> 01:35:09,294
CG-36500, YOU COPY?

869
01:35:12,881 --> 01:35:14,391
IF THEY KNOW WHERE THEY ARE...

870
01:35:15,134 --> 01:35:17,896
SOMEONE TELL ME WHERE I AM BECAUSE
I DON'T KNOW WHERE THE HELL WE ARE.

871
01:35:17,922 --> 01:35:19,749
WEBBER, DO YOU COPY?

872
01:35:20,349 --> 01:35:25,321
I'M NOT GOING OUT TO SEA...NO.
THIS IS STATION CHATHAM, DO YOU COPY?

873
01:35:25,388 --> 01:35:30,911
WE JUST GOT YOU OFF A BOAT,
THERE'S NO WAY WE'RE GONNA GET YOU ALL UP THERE.

874
01:35:30,978 --> 01:35:33,598
CG-36500, THIS IS STATION CHATHAM.

875
01:35:33,765 --> 01:35:39,747
WEBBER, YOUR ORDERS ARE TO PROCEED 5 MILES NORTHEAST
AND ONBOARD ALL SURVIVORS AT THE POLLOCK.

876
01:35:55,015 --> 01:35:59,311
SOUNDS LIKE THERE'S A CUT ON THE RADIO, MR.CLUFF.
HE'S GOING AT ON HIS OWN.

877
01:36:00,638 --> 01:36:01,889
BERNIE WEBBER.

878
01:36:03,558 --> 01:36:04,768
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

879
01:36:04,799 --> 01:36:06,301
HOW DO THEY GET HOME?

880
01:36:06,324 --> 01:36:08,017
HE TURNED OFF HIS RADIO.

881
01:36:10,567 --> 01:36:13,403
POOR GUYS! I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS IS HAPPENING.

882
01:36:22,122 --> 01:36:23,590
THERE'S SOME MORE STUFF IN THE CAR.

883
01:36:30,515 --> 01:36:32,342
THE POWER WENT OUT.
HOW DO THEY GET HOME?

884
01:36:32,390 --> 01:36:33,816
POWERS OUT.

885
01:36:34,928 --> 01:36:38,057
THE WHOLE TOWN! THE POWERS OUT.

886
01:36:39,275 --> 01:36:41,903
IT'S WORSE THAN LAST YEAR.
YOU NEVER KNOW.

887
01:37:00,258 --> 01:37:01,885
LET'S GET TO THE PIER.

888
01:37:12,325 --> 01:37:14,200
HOW DID YOU FIND US WITHOUT A COMPASS?

889
01:37:16,783 --> 01:37:20,992
WE...WE JODGED WITH SEASONAL CURRENTS.

890
01:37:25,575 --> 01:37:27,575
THINK WE JUST GOT LUCKY.

891
01:37:27,675 --> 01:37:28,875
YEAH.

892
01:37:32,200 --> 01:37:33,442
LUCKY.

893
01:37:37,075 --> 01:37:38,825
WELL, YOU KNOW HOW YOU GET HOME?

894
01:37:40,200 --> 01:37:42,408
TO BE HONEST WITH YA, I'M NOT SURE.

895
01:37:44,358 --> 01:37:50,325
JUST, DISOBEYED ALL MY RANKING OFFICERS.
THEY DON'T KNOW. SO I'M BETTER THAN 'EM, ALRIGHT?

896
01:37:51,075 --> 01:37:53,367
BUT THE WIND ON MY LEFT GOIN' OUT.

897
01:37:53,825 --> 01:37:59,575
EVEN IF I...KEEP IT ON THE RIGHT,
WE OUGHT TO BE THERE IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION.

898
01:38:02,492 --> 01:38:06,200
WE JUST FOLLOW ALL THE LIGHTS ON THE SHORE.
FOLLOW THE LIGHTS ON THE SHORE.

899
01:38:19,492 --> 01:38:21,617
WELL, WE ARE IN YOUR HANDS, CAPTAIN.

900
01:38:31,575 --> 01:38:32,733
LISTEN UP.

901
01:38:36,992 --> 01:38:39,075
I PUT THE SEA BEHIND US.

902
01:38:41,033 --> 01:38:43,825
JUST LET IT PUSH US ALONG,
TILL WE LAND SOMEWHERE.

903
01:38:43,992 --> 01:38:49,367
STORM'S EASING' UP BOYS, SO..WE JUST LOOK
AT THE SHORE LIGHTS TO GUIDE US IN.

904
01:38:49,533 --> 01:38:55,533
EVEN IF WE HAVE TO GO SO FAR AS NOBSKA POINT.
SO BE IT! WE JUST GONNA FIND LAND!

905
01:39:00,075 --> 01:39:03,158
BEEN ONE HECK OF A LONG DAY, RIGHT FELLAS?

906
01:39:03,783 --> 01:39:06,908
YEAH, SURE HAS!

907
01:39:08,992 --> 01:39:11,533
BUT DON'T YOU GIVE UP HOPE ON ME NOW.

908
01:39:13,742 --> 01:39:16,200
IT'S A GOOD BOAT.
WILL GET US THROUGH.

909
01:39:18,617 --> 01:39:21,608
WILL GET YOU HOME, OKAY?
WE ARE ALL GOIN' HOME.

910
01:39:23,242 --> 01:39:24,908
WE ARE WITH YOU, SKIPPER.

911
01:42:49,575 --> 01:42:53,375
KEEP THE LIGHTS ON, LIKE SHE'S DOIN'.
TURN YOUR LIGHTS ON.

912
01:42:53,442 --> 01:42:56,700
TURN ON THE LIGHTS, EVERYONE.

913
01:42:57,367 --> 01:42:59,533
MORE LIGHT, SO THAT THEY CAN SEE US.

914
01:43:49,283 --> 01:43:51,575
I THINK WE MADE IT OVER THE BAR.

915
01:43:55,117 --> 01:43:57,442
THE THICK TIDE THERE IS OVER!

916
01:43:57,608 --> 01:44:00,525
YOU SEE THAT!?

917
01:44:22,617 --> 01:44:25,342
FITZ, TURN ON THE SEARCHLIGHT.

918
01:44:56,875 --> 01:45:01,088
LOOK, YOU SEE THAT?
THERE ARE OUR BOYS!

919
01:45:12,083 --> 01:45:13,333
IS IT THEM?

920
01:45:16,150 --> 01:45:17,758
WELL DONE, BERNIE.

921
01:45:18,283 --> 01:45:21,867
YOU DID IT, WEBBER!
WELL DONE, WEBBER!

922
01:45:22,742 --> 01:45:25,617
36500 CHATHAM DOCKING AT THE CHATHAM PIER.

923
01:45:25,783 --> 01:45:30,050
APPEAR TO BE 32 SURVIVORS, SIR.
I REPEAT: WE HAVE 32 SURVIVORS.

924
01:45:51,975 --> 01:45:53,542
ATTA BOY! BERNIE.

925
01:46:04,375 --> 01:46:05,667
GIVE ME THE END.

926
01:46:06,617 --> 01:46:08,217
CMON! GOOD TO SEE YOU.
COME ON OVER.

927
01:46:08,283 --> 01:46:10,708
TAKE IT EASY!

928
01:46:11,575 --> 01:46:15,308
THIS MAN'S FREEZING. GIVE HIM A COAT.
GO ON IN, IT'S WARM INSIDE.

929
01:46:17,283 --> 01:46:18,783
LET'S GET YOU IN THE LODGE.

930
01:46:18,950 --> 01:46:21,250
NICE AND EASY. I GOT YA.

931
01:46:36,225 --> 01:46:37,775
GOOD JOB, CAPTAIN.

932
01:46:41,392 --> 01:46:42,725
WELL DONE, BERNIE.

933
01:46:56,005 --> 01:46:57,705
WEBBER?

934
01:47:24,017 --> 01:47:25,483
BERNIE.

935
01:48:05,325 --> 01:48:06,833
LET'S GO.

936
01:48:40,167 --> 01:48:42,375
WE STILL GOT 5 DAYS UNTIL APRIL 16.

937
01:48:42,475 --> 01:48:43,975
YEAH...

938
01:48:45,733 --> 01:48:47,575
I ASKED CLUFF FOR YOU.

939
01:48:49,175 --> 01:48:51,442
HE SAID IT'S JUST A...
FORMALITY.

940
01:48:53,317 --> 01:48:55,042
NOW I KNOW, RIGHT?

941
01:49:39,499 --> 01:49:40,409
THE END

942
01:49:40,940 --> 01:49:50,950
